    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine sanctae et individuae trinitatis. <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/77">Heinricus</persName> quartus divina favente clementia
                            <rs key="#Emperor/king">rex</rs> secundum voluntatem dei salvatoris
                        nostrique liberatoris. Quicquid confirmationis et proprietatis ad
                        aecclesiarum dei sanctorumque suorum exaltationem prebuerimus, id nobis ad
                        aeterne beatitudinis bravium et saecularis vite profectum esse profuturum
                        verissime credimus. Igitur omnium sancte dei aecclesiae fidelium
                        nostrorumque praesentium scilicet ac futurorum agnoscat universitas,
                        qualiter nos pro dei omnipotentis amore et patris nostri nostraeque anime
                        remedio, interventu quoque <persName key="#Bishops"><name ref="Oddo"
                                >Odonis</name></persName>
                        <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/406"><placeName ref="#places/245"
                                >Nouariensis</placeName></orgName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">episcopi</rs> et <persName key="#Count"><name
                                ref="Everardus">Hebrardi</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Count">comitis</rs> nostri fidelissimi, Adalberti etiam Alemanni
                        Brixiensis vexilliferi <rs key="#Monasteries">coenobio</rs> ad honorem
                            <orgName
                            key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis #Offersio/donatio #Rivers #Mountains #Villas #Curtes #Massae #Mansi #Landed_possessions #Forests #Fisheries #Saltworks #Penalty #Wine #Hay/fodder #Fiscal_property #Castle #Angaria #Teloneum #Immunity #Exemption #Churches #Monasteries #Abbots #Monks #Royal_slave #Royal_aldius"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/3619">sancti Salvatoris</orgName> haut procul a
                        moenibus <placeName ref="#places/65">Ticinensis</placeName> urbis fundato
                        per hoc nostrum <rs key="#Imperial/royal_diploma">regale praeceptum</rs>,
                        prout iuste et legaliter valemus, confirmamus, quemadmodum per antecessores
                        meos preceptali auctoritate confirmata sunt, omnia, quae eidem venerabili
                        loco donata collata et oblata sunt tam largifluo munere <persName
                            key="#Offersio/donatio #Queen" ref="#people/1301">Adheleidis</persName>
                        <rs key="#Queen">imperatricis</rs> auguste quam etiam aliqua inscriptione
                        cartarum aliorum hominum, cum <rs key="#Castle">castellis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Curtes">curtibus</rs>
                        <rs key="#Royal_slave">servis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Royal_slave">ancillis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Royal_aldius">aldianibus</rs> et <rs key="#Royal_aldius"
                            >aldianis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Churches">capellis</rs> oratoriis <rs key="#Villas">villis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Mansi">mansis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Landed_possessions">campis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Wine">vineis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Hay/fodder">pratis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Hay/fodder">pascuis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Forests">silvis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Mountains">montibus</rs> vallibus planiciebus <rs key="#Rivers"
                            >aquis aquarumque decursibus</rs>
                        <rs key="#Fisheries">piscationibus</rs>
                        <rs key="#Mills">molendinis</rs> terris cultis et incultis <rs
                            key="#Tolls #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters">ripis</rs>
                        <rs key="#Ports">portibus</rs>, verum etiam cum omnibus, de quibus idem
                        venerabile coenobium iuste investituram habet vel habuit ex ea die, qua
                        prefata serenissima imperatrix <rs key="#Monks">monachos</rs> ibi
                        constituit. Confirmamus quidem et firmissima traditione largimur eidem
                        monasterio domini Salvatoris monasterium <orgName
                            key="#Monasteries #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                            #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >sancti Anastasii</orgName> una cum <rs key="#Curtes">curte</rs>
                        <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/139"><placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ref="#places/342">Olonna</placeName></geogName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Montecelli</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Erbariam</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Basiliguciam</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Frisinariam</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Pastorianum</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Riuoceruinum</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Tullianum</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Puiholum</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Centascum</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Noue</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Urbam</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/18">Marincum</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Corianum</placeName> cum omnibus pertinentiis suis, <rs key="#Castle"
                            >castellum</rs> de <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                    #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                            >Bosco</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                        #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                            >Felegariolam</placeName>, terram de <persName
                            key="#Landed_possessions
                            #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                            #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches">
                            <name ref="Petrus Albesanus">Petro Albesano</name></persName>, terram
                        quam tenuit <persName
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                            #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                ><name ref="Liudualdus">Liutaldus</name></persName> cum <rs
                            key="#Mansi">manso</rs> de <placeName
                            key="#Mansi #Fiscal_property #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches">
                            <geogName key="#Mansi #Fiscal_property #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >Pelenzona</geogName></placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                    #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                            >Armentariam</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                        #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                            >Blundum</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                            #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                            >Gagium</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                                #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                            >Lagus ianum</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                                    #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                            >Cassinam</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                                        #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                            >Cuguzudam</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                            #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                            >Garlascum</placeName> cum <rs key="#Other_administrative_unit"
                            >districtu</rs> in circuitu duobus miliariis una cum <rs key="#Forests"
                            >silva</rs> de <placeName
                            key="#Forests #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                            #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Castle"
                            >Carbonaria</placeName>, de quanto iam dictum monasterium per praeceptum
                        tenere videtur, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                            #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Uirgemini</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Cauconate</placeName>, viridiarium prope palatinam portam et sancti
                        Iohannis scitum cum omnibus pertinentiis et adiacentiis suis tam infra
                        civitatem Ticinensem quam extra, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                            #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Garfinianam</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Uicumlongum</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                    #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Bissione</placeName>, cellam <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                        #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            >sancti Nazarii</orgName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                            #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Mauraticam</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                                #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Melariam</placeName>; insuper monasterium <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence
                                                    #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Monasteries"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1460">sancte dei genitricis Marie</orgName> in
                        loco <placeName ref="#places/4179">Pomposo</placeName> constructum cum
                        quibus ad illud pertinere videntur, vel etiam omnes <rs key="#Saltworks"
                            >salinas</rs>, que in <placeName key="#Saltworks" ref="#places/485"
                            >Comaclo</placeName> ad supra scriptum monasterium domini Salvatoris
                        pertinere decernuntur, seu in omnibus aliis locis, que iam dicto coenobio
                        sancti Salvatoris pertinere cernuntur, illi in proprium corroboramus.
                        Precipientes itaque iubemus, ut <rs key="#Immunity #Exemption">nullus
                            episcopus dux marchio comes vicecomes gastaldio nullaque nostri regni
                            magna parvaque persona de rebus mobilibus sive immobilibus sive de
                            qualibet terra disvestire idem monasterium sine legali iudicio
                            presumat</rs>. Sanctimus insuper et hac nostra regali auctoritate
                        concedimus, ut, si contigerit, quod sepe accidit, quatinus <rs key="#Abbots"
                            >abbas</rs> praenominati monasterii huius lucis habitaculum deserat,
                        liceat monachos ex sinu eiusdem ecclesiae quem meliorem viderint eligere in
                        patrem, omnium episcoporum vel omnium mortalium contradictione remota, nec
                        fas sit alicui monacho ex alio monasterio ad id transitum facere sine
                        voluntate monachorum inibi deo servientium in perpetuum. Si quis autem huius
                        nostre promulgate auctoritatis et praecepti violator extiterit sive
                        [prae]dicte e+cclesiae sancti Salvatoris minorationem facere aut in
                        castellis villis vel in aliquibuslibet locis eius aribergare, <rs
                            key="#Assembly">placitum</rs> sine eiusdem coenobii abbatis iussione
                        ullatenus tenere aut aliquam <rs key="#Angaria">angariam</rs> vel puplicam
                        functionem aut <rs key="#Teloneum">ttheloneum</rs> extorquere vel tollere
                        aut monachos de aliqua re presumpserit molestare, sciat se compositurum <rs
                            key="#Penalty">auri cocti libras mille</rs>, <rs key="#Camera_regis"
                            >medietatem camere nostre</rs> et <rs
                            key="#Camera_of_other_public_authorities">medietatem abbati eiusdem
                            monasterii</rs>, qui pro tempore fuerit, et insuper, quod ei deterius
                        est, cum Iuda traditore domini Salvatoris, in cuius nomine iam dictum
                        monasterium constructum est, eternis deputetur incendiis. Ut autem verius
                        credatur hoc pre+ceptum nostra auctoritate peractum, presentem paginam manu
                        propria, ut videtur infra, corroborantes sigillo nostro iussimus insigniri.
                        Signum domni Heinrici (M.) quarti regis invictissimi. (SI. D.) <persName
                            key="#Chancellor #Bishops" ref="#people/366">Gregorius</persName>
                        <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/81">Vercellensis</orgName> episcopus ac <rs
                            key="#Chancellor">cancellarius</rs> vice domni <persName
                            key="#Archchancellor #Archbishops"><name ref="Ildolfus"
                            >Hitolfi</name></persName> Coloniensis archiepiscopi et <rs
                            key="#Archchancellor">archicancellarii</rs> recognovit. Data III non.
                        aprili anno ab incarnatione domini nostri Ihsu Christi millesimo LXXVII,
                        indictione XV, anno autem ordinationis quidem domni Heinrici quarti regis
                        XXVI, regni vero XXIIII; actum <placeName ref="#places/65"
                        >Papie</placeName>; feliciter amen.</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
